  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Resilience Plus: Bolstering Recovery from Niger&apos;s Food Crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Intermediate Result 1: Communal land has conservation structures in place to improve soil and water retention
 - Intermediate Result 2: Most vulnerable households access quality certified millet and cowpeas seeds and low-cost storage materials
 - Intermediate Result 3: Men and women producers have improved knowledge and skills on improved agricultural production and storage techniques for food crops 
 - Intermediate Result 4: Women agro-pastoralists have improved knowledge and skills on care and fattening of small ruminants for sale
 - Intermediate Result 5: Institutional strengthening for farmers associations in governance and marketing</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of this project is to ensure the most vulnerable populations in Tahoua, Niger recover from the 2012 food crisis and are more resilient to climate shocks.</narrative>
  </description>
